net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler

Class CompilerOperatorTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.expr.AbstractOperatorTable
      • net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler.CompilerOperatorTable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OperatorTable

    public class CompilerOperatorTable
extends AbstractOperatorTable
    The operator table used by the EFA compilers. In addition to providing access to operators by names as defined by the OperatorTable interface, this class facilitates semantic access to logical and assignment operators.
    Author:
    Robi Malik

      • getAssigningOperator

        public BinaryOperator getAssigningOperator(BinaryOperator op)
        Retrieves the arithmetic operator for modifying assignment operators such as +=. For example, the assigning operator of += is +. If the given operator is not an assignment, or the normal assignment operator =, then null is returned.

      • getNegatedSubterm

        public SimpleExpressionProxy getNegatedSubterm(SimpleExpressionProxy expr)
        Checks whether the given expression is a not-expression.
        Parameters:
        expr - The expression to be checked.
        Returns:
        If the given expression is a not-expression, its subterm is returned, otherwise null is returned.
